Question: Inform if below code will pass or give errors? What will happen?

Stream<Integer> st = list.stream().map(e -> e);
st.findFirst();
st.findFirst();

Answer:
This code will throw a java.lang.IllegalStateException.

Reason:
A Java Stream can be consumed only once.
When you call a terminal operation like findFirst(), the stream gets closed.

So:

1) First call

st.findFirst();

This is a terminal operation

The stream st is consumed/closed

2️)Second call

st.findFirst();

Now the stream is already closed

Java throws:
Exception in thread "main" java.lang.IllegalStateException: stream has already been operated upon or closed



==
import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.stream.Stream;

public class Code {
    public static void main(String args[]){
        List<Integer> list = Arrays.asList(1,2,3,4,5);
        Stream<Integer> st = list.stream().map(e -> e);
        st.findFirst();
        st.findFirst();
    }
}
